<%- include('../partials/head', { title: 'About The Build' }) %>
<%- include('../partials/nav') %>
<%- include('../partials/disclaimer') %>
<main id="main" class="container">
  <%- include('../partials/flash') %>

  <section class="section-block about-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">About the build</p>
      <h1>USF Capital is a product demo dressed like a private capital lab.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The goal is to show how a serious investor-style platform can feel: clean onboarding,
        a live dashboard, allocation screens, security settings, synthetic market movement and a polished public brand.
      </p>
      <div class="kpi-grid">
        <div class="kpi-card"><strong><%= poolCount %></strong><span>simulated pools</span></div>
        <div class="kpi-card"><strong><%= lockYears %>Y</strong><span>illustrative cycle</span></div>
        <div class="kpi-card"><strong>$<%= totalCapDollars.toFixed(0) %></strong><span>fictional cap</span></div>
      </div>
      <p class="fine-print">The app is intentionally fictional. Its value is in the software architecture, interface design and end-to-end product flow.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-stack">
      <article class="card">
        <h2>What it demonstrates</h2>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>Express and EJS server-rendered pages.</li>
          <li>SQLite-backed users, sessions, positions and performance ticks.</li>
          <li>Demo identity flow, account security settings and optional 2FA.</li>
          <li>Synthetic charts, ticker movement and allocation logic.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h2>What it is not</h2>
        <p>This is not a live finance company, trading service, fund, exchange, custodian or advisory product. It is a portfolio-grade software simulation.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
